  	LOCATION;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:West Bloomfield High School
  	SUMMARY;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:WBHS Choir Singathon
  	CLASS:PUBLIC
  	DESCRIPTION;ENCODING=QUOTED-PRINTABLE:WHAT IS IT?\n A 9-hour, through-the-night, endless series of madcap fun, improvisational theatre games, music, creativity, food and mayhem all focused on two very good causes:\n\nRaising travel, uniform, and production expenses\nBringing a gaggle of kids together for one great evening of wildness at the start of the year.\n\n \n \nDETAILS PLEASE&hellip;\n\nAuditorium and in Laker Commons\nStudents participate in improvisational showcases featuring a varied level of bizarre skits, music, and other creative ideas.  Throughout the 9 hours, students are constantly regrouped into different &ldquo;production companies&rdquo; and prepare a series of performances based on ideas, props, and other prompts given by the director.  These include, but are no limited to:\nSong Improvisation:  6 people get a bag of unrelated items and an envelope with some thematic information.  The group must then work up a 1-3 minute song using all the items in the bag, the bag itself, revolving around the info in the envelope.\nThe Broadway Musical:  6-10 people are given the script and song for a scene from a musical and then, taking one hour, completely choreograph a Broadway-style song and dance number while lip-synching to the material.\nLive Music Video:  similar to Broadway Musical, but the material is a pop song that needs to be developed into as full blown a live-action music video as can be created in one hour.\nHypnosis show &ndash; Parent Mike Brody will perform his hypnotist show\nIs it Live or Is It Tape?  An improv based on a series of suggestions that is two-tiered&mdash;one group creates the &ldquo;song&rdquo; by way of a recording, the other must act it out.\nSomething new, bold, exciting, and totally unbelievable---we just have to think about what it is going to be first.\n&ldquo;Whose Line&hellip;&rdquo;:  We will use many of the songs and skits developed on the show (which actually come from many other sources) to fill in the gaps.\n\n \nHOW DO I GET INVOLVED?\nIt&rsquo;s really pretty simple, every choral member is eligible  All you need is $40 (garnered through sponsorships&mdash;more below), a two-litre bottle of pop, the entire 9-hour time span free of conflicts, and a willingness to have fun in a safe but wildly inventive manner.\n\nGet one of these sheets and read through it thoroughly.\nTake at least one, if not more, Singathon Sponsor Sheets and begin finding Sponsors for your involvement in the Singathon.\nThe student bringing in the most sponsorships will receive a choir t shirt and two tickets to the spring concert!!!\nPound pavement, ask friends, neighbors, family, to sponsor you for the event, collecting money all along the way and filling out the information on the sheet as you go.  Or you can simply offer to pay the entry fee on your own, too.\nBring yourself, your sponsor sheet (FILLED OUT BY EVERYONE AND SIGNED BY YOUR PARENTS), all the sponsor money (minimum $40), your two-litre bottle of pop, and anything else you think will help pass the night away to the auditorium on Friday, September 18th.  Please arrive no later than 9:30 pm so we can begin on time.  Students are encouraged to wear comfortable clothing (sometimes a change of clothing is good, too), along with special snacks they themselves are particularly fond of, but that no one else likes.\nAll food, snacks, etc, are provided throughout the night.\nNo cell phones permitted. Adults will have access to phones at all times.\nNo one will be permitted to leave the site unless an emergency arises.  This is not an event for which the participants are allowed to set their own time lines.\nThe event ends promptly at 6 am Saturday.  We must be vacated by 7 am that day so arrangements must be made ahead of time for rides, etc.\nThis event is fully chaperoned by a running roster of parents who serve in three hour shifts.  Several parents will spend the entire time with us, so supervision should not be a concern.\n\n \nIF YOU HAVE ANY QUESTIONS OR YOUR PARENTS WOULD LIKE TO GET INVOLVED, TOO (BY CHAPERONING ONE OF THE SHIFTS) PLEASE CALL THE Mrs. Hauk&rsquo;s cell at 248-935-7721 or check out the website for details at www.wbhschoirs.org
  	PRIORITY:0
  	END:VEVENT
